<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en"
      lang="en"
      metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
      i18n:domain="launchpad">

<head>
    <title metal:fill-slot="title">Soyuz: Linux Distribution
    Management</title>
    <!-- Plone style sheet -->
    <style type="text/css" media="screen">@import url(plone.css);</style>
    <!-- Soyuz style sheet -->
    <style type="text/css" media="screen">@import url(soyuz.css);</style>
</head>

<body>

<div metal:fill-slot="main">

    <h1>Welcome to Soyuz!</h1>

    <p class="documentDescription">
    Soyuz is a Linux Distribution Management System. It allows you to create
    your own Linux distribution, selecting the packages that you want to
    include in the distro, managing uploads and builds across multiple
    architectures, and ultimately giving you an installation CD and
    Live CD. Read more <a href="+about">about Soyuz</a>.
    </p>


    <p>Please select a distribution from the list below:</p>

    <table width="100%" class="listing rowNavigation">
        <tr>
            <th>Name</th>
            <th>Title</th>
            <th>Homepage</th>
        </tr>
        <tr tal:repeat="distro context/distributions"
            tal:attributes="onclick
                string:window.location='distros/${distro/name}'">
            <td tal:content="distro/name">distro</td>
            <td tal:content="distro/title">distribution title</td>
            <td tal:content="distro/domainname">http://www.domain.com/</td>
        </tr>
    <ul>

   </div>
  </body>
</html>
